{"lemma": "حارٌّ", "slug": "حارٌّ", "root": "ح.#.ر", "root_slug": "ح-_-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ح-_-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["adj", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n7522", "n7804", "n9444", "n9714"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "hot", "fa": "داغ", "ur": "گرم", "tr": "sıcak", "id": "panas", "bn": "গরম", "es": "caliente", "fr": "chaud", "de": "heiß", "ru": "жаркий", "zh": "热的"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "hot, burning"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to return, to come back, to recoil"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to change the state, to be converted"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Derived from the active participle of حَرَّ (ḥarra, “to be hot”).\nCompare Hebrew חריף (kharíf)."}, "ipa": ["/ħaːrr/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n7522", "headword_ar": "حَارٌّ", "root": "Hr", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Hot:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) a"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "very hot"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "day, and food. (A.) IAar says, I do not say ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomN Har~N", "text_ar": "يَوْمٌ حَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qr", "text_ar": "قر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) [This seems to imply that some allow it; and it is common in the present day. See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaromN", "text_ar": "جَرْمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b2-  See an ex. of its fem.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAr~ap", "text_ar": "حَارَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the next preceding paragraph. ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Difficult, troublesome, distressing, fatiguing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "severe"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "work. (K, TA.) El-Hasan, when [his father] 'Alee ordered him to flog El-Weleed the son of 'Okbeh for drinking wine, in the days of 'Othmán, said,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wal~i", "text_ar": "وَلِّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAr~ahaA mano tawal~aY qaAr~ahaA", "text_ar": "حَارَّهَا مَنْ تَوَلَّى قَارَّهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Set thou over what is evil thereof him who has superintended what is good thereof:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "set thou over what is difficult of the affair him who has superintended what is profitable thereof:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) meaning that only he should undertake the infliction of the flogging who superintends the profitable affairs of government. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaA='a fulaAnN HaAr~FA mux~uhu", "text_ar": "جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ حَارًّا مُخُّهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAr~a AlEiZaAmi", "text_ar": "حَارَّ العِظَامِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one came in a plump,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fat, state; contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAridFA mux~uhu", "text_ar": "بَارِدًا مُخُّهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baArida AlEiZaAmi", "text_ar": "بَارِدَ العِظَامِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (A and TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "brd", "text_ar": "برد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "Mgh"]}, {"entry_id": "n7804", "headword_ar": "حَارٍ", "root": "HrY", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "masc. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAriyapN", "text_ar": "حَارِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, TA,) which is an epithet applied to a viper ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afoEFY", "text_ar": "اَفْعًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "); (S, M, K;) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That has decreased in its body by reason of age;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and it is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the worst,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "most malignant"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "noxious, that is:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that has become old, and has wasted in its body, and whereof there remains not save its head and its breath"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nafasuhaA", "text_ar": "نَفَسُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nafosuhaA", "text_ar": "نَفْسُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "])"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and its poison:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K:) dim. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuwayorK", "text_ar": "حُوَيْرٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ramaAka A@ll~`hu biA^afoEFY HaAriyapK", "text_ar": "رَمَاكَ ا@للّٰهُ بِاَفْعًى حَارِيَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God smile thee with an evil like a viper wasted by age"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.)"}], "source_refs": ["M", "TA", "S", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n9444", "headword_ar": "حَارَ", "root": "Hwr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaHuwru", "text_ar": "يَحُورُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaworN", "text_ar": "حَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Huw^uwrN", "text_ar": "حُوُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuwrN", "text_ar": "حُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", a contraction of the form next preceding, used in poetry, in case of necessity, (TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maHaArN", "text_ar": "مَحَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maHaArapN", "text_ar": "مَحَارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaworapN", "text_ar": "حَوْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, returned,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, L, K,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilaY $aYo'K", "text_ar": "اـِلَى شَىْءٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to a thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eanohu", "text_ar": "عَنْهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HAr Ealayohi", "text_ar": "حار عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a false imputation)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "returned to him"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[who was its author; or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "recoiled upon him"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaArati AlguS~apu", "text_ar": "حَارَتِ الغُصَّةُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The thing sticking in the throat, and choking, descended;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as though it returned from its place. (TA.) ―         -b4-  [And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HAr", "text_ar": "حار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaworN", "text_ar": "حَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuwrN", "text_ar": "حُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He returned from a good state to a bad."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HAr baEoda maA kaAna", "text_ar": "حار بَعْدَ مَا كَانَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA on the authority of 'Ásim, and so in a copy of the S,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He returned from a good state after he had been in that state:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A 'Obeyd, S, * TA:) so says 'Asim: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HAr bEd mA kaAra", "text_ar": "حار بعد ما كَارَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA, and so in copies of the S,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He became in a state of defectiveness after he had been in a state of redundance:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or it is from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HAr", "text_ar": "حار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaworN", "text_ar": "حَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He untwisted"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "his turban: (Zj, TA:) and means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He became in a bad state of affairs after he had been in a good state."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA. [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaworN", "text_ar": "حَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", below.]) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAra wabaAra", "text_ar": "حَارَ وَبَارَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He became in a defective and bad state."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA. [Here"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bAr", "text_ar": "بار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an imitative sequent; (see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAy^irN", "text_ar": "حَايِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";) as is also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yabuwru", "text_ar": "يَبُورُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in a phrase mentioned below.]) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HAr", "text_ar": "حار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor. as above, (Msb,) inf n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaworN", "text_ar": "حَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Msb, K) and"}, {"k